ay to an achievable future in which democratically determined values guide AI to be peaceful in its intent; to embrace limitations; to serve purpose, not profit; and to be firmly rooted in societal trust.AI Needs You gives us hope that we, the people, can imbue AI with a deep intentionality that reflects our best values, ideals, and interests, and that serves the public good. AI will permeate our lives in unforeseeable ways, but it is clear that the shape of AI’s future—and of our own—cannot be left only to those building it. It is up to us to guide this technology away from our worst fears and toward a future that we can trust and believe in.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aArtificial intelligencexSocial aspects. 0aTechnological innovationsxSocial aspects. 0aTechnology and civilization. 0aTechnology and state. 7aCOMPUTERS / Intelligence (AI) & Semantics.2bisacsh  aAI Bill of Rights.  aAI Needs You: How We Can Change AI's Future and Save Our Own.  aAI education: AI public good.  aAI ethics.  aAI fear: Artificial intelligence.  aAI governance.  aAI regulation.  aAI’s power grows.  aArtificial intelligence.  aAtomic Bomb.  aBing.  aChatGPT.  aChatbot.  aCold War.  aDeepMind.  aEmbryo research/human embryology.  aGoogle.  aIVF (in vitro fertilization).  aLarge Language Models (LLMs).  aLouise Joy Brown.  aOnline security.  aOpenAI.  aOppenheimer.  aRoe V. Wade.  aSilicon Valley.  aSpace Race.  aTimes 100 AI.  aUnited Nations Outer Space Treaty 1967.  aWarnock Commission.  abetter education.  abetter society.  abiotech.  achatgpt.  acritical.  ademocracy geopolitics.  afuture of AI.  agenerative ai.  aharmful.  ahistory of science.  ahistory.  ahow can AI help: AI policy.  ahow we can safeguard AI’s future for the public good.  